.TH PLSMEM 3plplot  "May, 2005" "" "PLplot API"
.SH NAME
\fBplsmem\fP - Set the memory area to be plotted 
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBplsmem\fP(\fImaxx\fP, \fImaxy\fP, \fIplotmem\fP)
.SH DESCRIPTION

.P
Set the memory area to be plotted (with the mem driver) as the dev member of the stream structure.  Also set the number of pixels in the memory passed in \fIplotmem\fP, which is a block of memory \fImaxy\fP by \fImaxx\fP by 3 bytes long, say: 480 x 640 x 3 (Y, X, RGB) 
.P
This memory will have to be freed by the user! 
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fImaxx\fP (PLINT, input) 
Size of memory area in the X coordinate. 
.TP
\fImaxy\fP (PLINT, input) 
Size of memory area in the Y coordinate. 
.TP
\fIplotmem\fP (void *, input) 
Pointer to the beginning of the user-supplied memory area. 

